OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1778695868
OL,3,CMarket concerns intensify as
OL,4,CWestminster descends into chaos again
OL,6,FOn financial markets, the jungle drums
OL,7,Fhave started to beat again.
OL,9,FThe pound has slipped; investors have
OL,10,Fbeen selling government bonds. As a
OL,11,Fbackdrop to events in Westminster, it
OL,12,Fall feels foreboding and familiar.
OL,14,FThe market moves are clearly not a
OL,15,Fvote of confidence in the UK's
OL,16,Fprospects, but how should we interpret
OL,17,Fthem?
OL,19,FA vote of no confidence in the prime
OL,20,Fminister? A comment on who might
OL,21,Fsucceed him?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1778695868
OL,3,CMarket concerns intensify as
OL,4,CWestminster descends into chaos again
OL,6,FThe "markets" are often personified,
OL,7,Fbut they don't think or speak as one.
OL,9,FThe term is a useful shorthand for a
OL,10,Fvast network of buyers and sellers
OL,11,Ftrading financial assets around the
OL,12,Fworld.
OL,14,FMarkets put a price on risk, in this
OL,15,Fcase, lending money to the UK
OL,16,Fgovernment, and politics is only one
OL,17,Ffactor in that calculation.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
