OL,3,CMarket concerns intensify as
OL,4,CWestminster descends into chaos again
OL,6,FIn recent months, investors have been
OL,7,Fcharging the UK a premium to borrow,
OL,8,Frelative to many other wealthy
OL,9,Fcountries.
OL,11,FThis is partly because we appear more
OL,12,Fvulnerable to the inflation the war in
OL,13,Fthe Gulf has caused, and also because
OL,14,Fthere is a perception that the Bank of
OL,15,FEngland will therefore have to keep
OL,16,Finterest rates higher for longer.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1778695868
OL,3,CMarket concerns intensify as
OL,4,CWestminster descends into chaos again
OL,6,FIt's worth noting that the market
OL,7,Fprice of oil and gas has risen in
OL,8,Frecent days, too, as hopes that the
OL,9,Fconflict may be coming to an end have
OL,10,Fonce again diminished.
OL,12,FThe "yield" - the effective interest
OL,13,Frate the government pays to borrow
OL,14,Fmoney - has risen by around 20 basis
OL,15,Fpoints on ten-year bonds in the last
OL,16,Ftwo days.
OL,26,@tD@EOUtD@KO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1778695868
OL,3,CMarket concerns intensify as
OL,4,CWestminster descends into chaos again
OL,6,F"This is not solely a political issue,
OL,7,Fbut the increase in the 10-year yield,
OL,8,Faccompanied by a fall in the pound,
OL,9,Ftells me politics is playing a big
OL,10,Fpart here," Paul Dales of Capital
OL,11,FEconomics said.
OL,13,FDales reads the market moves as
OL,14,Finvestors pricing in an increased
OL,15,Fprobability that Keir Starmer will be
OL,16,Freplaced at some point by someone who
OL,17,Fwould shift government policy to the
OL,18,Fleft.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@KO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1778695868
OL,3,CMarket concerns intensify as
OL,4,CWestminster descends into chaos again
OL,6,FAnd that someone like Angela Rayner or
OL,7,FAndy Burnham would be more inclined to
OL,8,Fborrow more, and that, in turn, is
OL,9,Fmore likely to put upward pressure on
OL,10,Finflation and interest rates.
OL,12,FAll this is educated guesswork, but
OL,13,Fthe rise in bond yields is real and
OL,14,Fhas real-world consequences.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
