CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1778695868
OL,3,CMarket concerns intensify as
OL,4,CWestminster descends into chaos again
OL,6,FMarkets don't control the government,
OL,7,Fbut they do set constraints on what it
OL,8,Fcan afford to do - and sharp changes
OL,9,Fin market prices can force the hand of
OL,10,Fthe government of the day.
OL,12,FLiz Truss was compelled to reverse her
OL,13,Ftax cuts and then stand down as prime
OL,14,Fminister in 2022 after investors
OL,15,Freacted strongly to her mini-Budget.
OL,17,FJohn Major had to withdraw the pound
OL,18,Ffrom the Exchange Rate Mechanism in
OL,19,F1992 after speculators began to bet
OL,20,Fagainst it.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/10
